            <para>
                <exhotlnk document="../recalls/Rec05514.pdf" bookname="RECALL">Print ready (PDF file) copy of the dealer
                    letter
                </exhotlnk>
            </para>
            <para>
                <exhotlnk document="../recalls/Cus05514.pdf" bookname="RECALL">Print ready (PDF file) copy of the
                    customer letter
                </exhotlnk>
            </para>
            <para>The positive battery cable between the batteries and the starter may rub against an electrical ground
                cable between the starter and frame rail possibly causing an electrical short and/or fire. This may
                result in
                <emph type="bold">property damage, personal injury or death</emph>.
            </para>
            <para>
                <title>MODELS INVOLVED</title>
            </para>
            <para>This Safety Recall involves 9000 models built at the Chatham, Ontario manufacturing facility 4/1/2002
                thru 6/15/2005 and 9000 models built at the Escobedo, Mexico manufacturing facility 4/1/2002 thru
                5/25/2004.
            </para>
        </defect>
        <ownernote>
            <para>During the recall process a listing of owner names and addresses will be furnished to the involved
                dealers to enable dealers to follow up with owners and have the vehicles corrected. You must limit the
                use of this listing to this campaign because the list may contain information obtained from state motor
                vehicle registration records and the use of such motor vehicle registration data for purposes other than
                this campaign is a violation of law in several states.
            </para>
        </ownernote>
        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="9">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent serious eye injury, always wear safe eye protection when you perform vehicle
                        maintenance or service.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent unexpected movement of the vehicle and possible serious personal injury or death,
                        block the wheels to prevent the vehicle from moving in both directions.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">INSPECTION/REPLACEMENT PROCEDURE TABLE</emph>
            </para>
            <para>Please refer to Table 1 to determine which procedure to follow regarding battery cable gap
                measurement, battery cable inspection and saddle clamp installation.
            </para>
            <table id="t0551403" tblwidth="pg-wide">
                <title>Engine Configuration Based Service Procedure</title>
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="0.60*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.40*"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Engine Configuration</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Procedures Required to be Performed</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Caterpillar, Cummins ISX, Cummins ISM, w/o Fuel Filter</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Battery Cable GAP Measurement (required)</para>
                                <para>Battery Cable Inspection (if necessary)</para>
                                <para>Saddle Clamp Installation (if necessary)</para>
                                <para>FINAL INSPECTION (required)</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Cummins ISM, w/Fuel Filter</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Battery Cable Inspection (required)</para>
                                <para>Saddle Clamp Installation (required)</para>
                                <para>FINAL INSPECTION (required)</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>A Cummins ISM w/Gear Pump Mounted Fuel Filter will ALWAYS require the SADDLE CLAMP
                        INSTALLATION.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">BATTERY CABLE GAP MEASUREMENT</emph>
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="boldital">You may wish to cut a wooden, bulk hose, or cardboard template to perform
                    subsequent measurements. Template should be 1.5 inches (38mm) long.
                </emph>
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="boldital">DO NOT USE A METALLIC MEASURING DEVICE</emph>
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">For Cummins ISM w/ fuel filter, do not perform the gap measurement, skip to the
                    <emph type="bold">BATTERY CABLE INSPECTION PROCEDURE</emph>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">For Caterpillar, Cummins ISX, and Cummins ISM w/o fuel filter, perform the following gap
                    measurement.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Measure the smallest gap between the positive cable's conduit and the closest point to
                    the negative cable bolted to the frame rail. See Figure 1.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0551401" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../recallfigures/g0551401.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"
                         scalefitheight="392px"/>
                <caption>Figure 1 - Gap Measurement</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If the smallest gap is less than 1.5 inches (38mm) continue on to
                    <emph type="bold">BATTERY CABLE INSPECTION PROCEDURE</emph>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0551402" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../recallfigures/g0551402.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"
                         scalefitheight="392px"/>
                <caption>Figure 2 - Saddle Clamp Installation REQUIRED</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If the smallest gap is 1.5 inches (38mm) or LARGER, then no further inspection or saddle
                    clamp installation is necessary, skip to
                    <emph type="bold">FINAL INSPECTION</emph>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0551403" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../recallfigures/g0551403.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="392px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 3 - No Saddle Clamp Necessary - Skip to FINAL INSPECTION</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">BATTERY CABLE INSPECTION PROCEDURE</emph>
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">For ALL suspect vehicles, if the gap measured above is less than 1.5 inches (38mm),
                    perform the following battery cable inspection procedure.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect positive (red) battery cables, conduit and ground cable (black) in areas
                    indicated below:
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0551404" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../recallfigures/g0551404.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="392px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 4 - Engine Removed for Clarity</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If ANY indication of chafing or rubbing is evident, replace any affected cables and
                    continue to step 11.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If there is NO indication of chafing or rubbing, continue on to
                    <emph type="bold">SADDLE CLAMP INSTALLATION</emph>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">SADDLE CLAMP INSTALLATION</emph>
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Before installing the saddle clamp, ensure the battery cable conduit has not fallen past where
                        the saddle clamp will be installed.
                    </para>
                    <para>Reposition or replace the conduit as necessary.</para>
                    <para>Install the saddle clamp and strap-locks over the conduit on the battery cables.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">For Caterpillar, Cummins ISX, and Cummins ISM (w/o fuel filter), see Figure 5.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install saddle clamp and strap-locks as indicated below:</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0551405" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../recallfigures/g0551405.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="408px"
                         scalefitheight="352px"/>
                <caption>Figure 5 - w/o Fuel Filter</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">For Cummins ISM engines with fuel filter please see Figure 6.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install saddle clamp and strap locks as indicated below.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-route battery cables between the fuel filter and engine block.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Ensure battery cables do not touch fuel filter assembly or fittings.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f0551406" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../recallfigures/g0551406.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"
                         scalefitheight="352px"/>
                <caption>Figure 6 - Cummins ISM w/Fuel Filter</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>
                <emph type="boldital">Caterpillar Engine Warning</emph>
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>After performing this recall on vehicles with Caterpillar engines, please inspect the routing
                        of the ENGINE BLOCK ground cable.
                    </para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>
                        <emph type="bold">TO PREVENT CHAFING OF THE POSITIVE CABLES AGAINST THE ENGINE BLOCK GROUND
                            CABLE (SEE FIGURE 7), PLEASE ENSURE ENGINE BLOCK GROUND CABLE IS CLOCKED IN THE DOWNWARD (6
                            O'CLOCK) POSITION, SEE FIGURE 8.
                        </emph>
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f0551407" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../recallfigures/g0551407.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                         scalefitheight="352px"/>
                <caption>Figure 7 - Chafing may occur between Engine Block Ground and Newly Located Positive Cables
                </caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If NO rubbing or chafing is present between CAT ENGINE GROUND cable and battery cables, NO
                        re-clocking is necessary.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>
                        <emph type="bold">If rubbing or chafing of the ENGINE GROUND cable against the Battery Cables is
                            present,
                        </emph>
                        rotate and tighten the new ground cable on the starter terminal so it is straight down (6
                        o'clock position) and not contacting the starter positive cables, see Figure 8.
                    </para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <figure id="f0551408" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../recallfigures/g0551408.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="392px"
                         scalefitheight="352px"/>
                <caption>Figure 8 - Correct CAT (non-C15) Engine Block Ground Cable Routing</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0551408a" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../recallfigures/g0551408a.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="392px"
                         scalefitheight="352px"/>
                <caption>Figure 8a - Correct CAT C15 Engine Block Ground Cable Routing</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
        <svcproc svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="6">
            <title>FINAL INSPECTION</title>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Regardless of whether or not the saddle clamp was installed, please perform this final
                        inspection on
                        <emph type="bold">all</emph>
                        vehicles to ensure the electrical cables are properly routed.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Please inspect the starter electrical cable routing for rubbing or chafing in the following
                        areas:
                    </para>
                    <randlist type="dash">
                        <item>
                            <para>Battery Cables to frame rail.</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Battery Cables to FRAME ground cable.</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Battery Cables to ENGINE BLOCK ground cable.</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Battery Cables to starter case, starter terminal studs or other starter components and
                                wiring.
                            </para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Battery Positive Cable to BATTERY ground cable.</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Battery Positive Cable to FUEL FILTER housing.</para>
                        </item>
                    </randlist>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>It may be necessary to loosen and/or remove a battery cable to re-orient it.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>It may also be necessary to loosen/replace routing/clipping points (p-clamps, extension clips,
                        etc.) to facilitate a no-rub condition.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>See Figures below for a representation of rub conditions that require remedied.</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <figure id="f0451005" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../recallfigures/g0451005.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                         scalefitheight="392px"/>
                <caption>Figure 9 - Battery Cables to Frame Rail Rub</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Ensure battery cables are NOT chafing on frame rail</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0451005a" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../recallfigures/g0451005a.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                         scalefitheight="392px"/>
                <caption>Figure 9a - Battery Cables to Frame Ground Rub</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Ensure battery cables are NOT chafing on frame ground</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0451005b" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../recallfigures/g0451005b.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                         scalefitheight="392px"/>
                <caption>Figure 9b - Battery Cables to Engine Block Ground Rub</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Ensure battery cables are NOT chafing on engine ground</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0451005c" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../recallfigures/g0451005c.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                         scalefitheight="392px"/>
                <caption>Figure 9c - Battery Cables to Starter Case, Starter Terminal Studs or Other Starter Components
                    and Wiring
                </caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Ensure battery cables are NOT chafing on ANYTHING!</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0451005d" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../recallfigures/g0451005d.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                         scalefitheight="392px"/>
                <caption>Figure 9d - Battery POSITIVE Cables to Battery GROUND Cables</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Ensure battery cables are NOT chafing on ANYTHING!</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0451005e" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../recallfigures/g0451005e.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                         scalefitheight="392px"/>
                <caption>Figure 9e - Battery POSITIVE Cables Rubbing on Fuel Filter Housing (CAT Engine Shown, However
                    Condition May Also Exist on Cummins ISM)
                </caption>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
